The paper discusses signal and image processing applications, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of cs.SP (Signal Processing) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The focus on sparsity and the two main options for sparse modeling suggest that cs.LG (Machine Learning) may also be a relevant sub-category. The mention of two-dimensional finite difference operator and image processing further suggest that cs.CV (Computer Vision) may be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the mention of existing algorithms and theory suggest that cs.MM (Multimedia) may also be a relevant sub-category.
